Chelsea have been handed a major boost with Callum Hudson-Odoi returning to first-team training. The Blues’ England international forward has been sidelined with an Achilles tendon injury but is now back with his team-mates at Stamford Bridge The Blues forward has been out of action since April after he picked up an Achilles injury against Burnley. The 18- year-old looks set for a return ahead of schedule with his recovery expected to take six months. Chelsea on their twitter handle shared images of the winger in training, challenging his team-mates and passing the ball during a training session. The club posted on Twitter with the caption “CALLUM!!!” WITH Hudson-Odoi replying “Let’s go”, much to the delight of Chelsea’s fans.